The paper discusses Web usage mining, which involves analyzing user behavior on the Web. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the organization and retrieval of information from large collections of data. The paper also mentions personalization, which is a common topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the Semantic Web and linked data, which are related to Database (cs.DB) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions resource annotation, which involves natural language processing and falls under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
